com.intuit.wasabi.experiment

Interface Mutex

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MutexImpl

    public interface Mutex
    Interface to manipulate mutual exclusion object for experiments.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      List<Map> createExclusions(Experiment.ID experimentID, ExperimentIDList experimentIDList, UserInfo user)
      Creates a new mutual exclusion rule and adds it to the database
      void deleteExclusion(Experiment.ID expID1, Experiment.ID expID2, UserInfo user)
      Deletes a mutual exclusion relation between 2 experiments by removing it from the database.
      ExperimentList getExclusions(Experiment.ID experimentID)
      Queries the database and returns a list of experiments, with metadata, that are mutually exclusive with the specified experiment.
      ExperimentList getNotExclusions(Experiment.ID experimentID)
      Queries the database and returns a list of experiments, with metadata, that are NOT mutually exclusive with the specified experiment.

      • deleteExclusion

        void deleteExclusion(Experiment.ID expID1,
                     Experiment.ID expID2,
                     UserInfo user)
        Deletes a mutual exclusion relation between 2 experiments by removing it from the database.
        Parameters:
        expID1 - ID of experiment 1
        expID2 - ID of experiment 2
        user - the UserInfo who deleted the exclusion
        Throws:
        ExperimentNotFoundException - if expID_1 or expID_2 is null.
